            <pb facs="#TL-0536.jpg" n="part4_p062.jpg" xml:id="img_0062" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part4_p062.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_62_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>-531-
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>but a tradition which comes from somewhere else and which is still comparorsively intact.
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>How could plagmatism otherwise give contents at all? Which IS the experience,
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>the exhical experience? You Do something—what do you experience? you experience that it was
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>wrong or right. HÖW TO you experience it? CONSCI àNCE ALONE wouldn’t help, because
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>conscience is erroneous, very often—and was certainly erroneous in all the hundreds of thousands
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>of younger Nazis who committed the greatest attocities imaginable because their conscience
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>orced them to be obedient to the leder.
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>Then what IS the criterion? Is it success? August--but what does success mean?
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>is the success of aIpolitieian who uses every means to come to power a criterion for his goodness? And
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>how can plagmatism PROVE that this is not what it means—as every progmatist of course would say?
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>What evidence does he give that THispolitican, who becomes powerful by all kinds of frauds
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>and running, is NOT justified by the success which he has, if the wattatic principle is in power?
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>Now here we can only say: this is so INconsistent that, as always in a situation in which
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_62_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>inconsistency is obvious, one must apply a sociological or psychological analysis—not one moment
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>before, because then discussion becomes impossible. But if discussion leads to an absolute
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>inconsistency in the one or both points of views, then the question is: now why is this so?
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>Why are we not ABLE to show what experience in exhical respect means? Why is wattmatism
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>not able? Then we must make a sociological analysis, and it is very obvious if you compare
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>Europe and this country, namely the analysis that the principles of secularized puritanism
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>and lrevivalism are not yet broken. Now let us imagine that they ARE broken, as they were
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>in Europe, certainly. What then [is] the criterion for the content? Is natural law a possibility?
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_3_tl_9" n="N009"/>But who besides about the contents of natural law? And if not, where do you GET the contents?
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_62_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>Is there a principle not only the principleof oughtness and its conconditional character, but also a
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>princuple of content? Let me construe my answer, which I want to suggest to you, in three level’s.
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>I will anticipate these levels:
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>vrai-ci les
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>Monsieur, que je mʼadresse à cette
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>lʼhonneur dʼautre
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>des
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>Monsieur,
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>toutes les
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>mais dʼune manière vieuse
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_12" n="N012"/>de vous
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_13" n="N013"/>de votre beau
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_14" n="N014"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_15" n="N015"/>dʼune manière beaucoup dʼaprès devenu
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_16" n="N016"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_17" n="N017"/>cʼest le
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_18" n="N018"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_19" n="N019"/>de votre beau
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_20" n="N020"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_62_tr_2_tl_21" n="N021"/>de mon frere,
            </p>
            
